subject: oem-ibm: inband: Check lid is complete
commitMessage:
oem-ibm: inband: Check lid is complete

A lid file can be written in one or more write requests. Read
the header for the expected size to check if the lid has been
fully written. The file size should be the lid size listed in
the header minus the size of the header.

Change-Id: I0fa02af3e50f13b40cea2494471445918826d716
Signed-off-by: Adriana Kobylak <anoo@us.ibm.com>

No reason to read the whole uint16_t value, since we're just looking for the first digit. This avoids endianess issues.
Should this function implement completion codes other than PLDM codes to indicate that the file is not complete?

It's my understanding that pldm doesn't know if an additional write will be done for the same file, so maybe there's no need for a different completion code since pldm can't do anything about it, it still has to return success to the hypervisor, and then a 2nd write to the same file may or may not be requested afterwards.
